[size=6][center][b][color=#ff0000]D[/color]eep [color=#ff0000]D[/color]ungeon[/b][/center][/size][center][img]https://i.imgur.com/ARr1wVE.gif[/img][/center]

[center][size=3]A [b]YYTK[/b] mod that completely [u]overhauls[/u] the game's [color=#ff00ff][b]dungeon[/b][/color] by adding several entirely new dungeon [color=#00ffff][b]mechanics[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]weapons[/b][/color], [color=#ff00ff][b]monsters[/b][/color], and more!
[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][quote][b]Author's Note: Mod Difficulty & Customization[/b]

The [b]Deep Dungeon[/b] is meant to be a challenging and fun experience that makes every dungeon run feel unique. To help strike the right balance for everyone regarding difficulty, a [b]mod configuration file[/b] has been added. There are several [b]options[/b] in it allowing you to customize many aspects of the mod ranging from [b]difficulty settings[/b] to [b]quality of life[/b] options.

Before beginning your journey, be sure to take a brief moment to read the [b]Configuration[/b] section on this page to familiarize yourself with these options, and change them as you see fit. There is no right or wrong way to play and enjoy this mod. As it evolves more configuration options will be added, so be sure to check for new options after major updates.[/quote][/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Major Update: Version 1.0.0 (Coming Soon)[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]fifth major update[/u] to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] has arrived! This update includes [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color], [color=#00ffff][b]system changes[/b][/color], and [color=#00ffff][b]bug fixes[/b][/color]!

[b][color=#ffff00]Divine Judgement[/color][/b]: The first [u]advanced class[/u], the [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle[/b][/color], has been added. The set bonus effects for this class have been designed to make the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] an even more dynamic and chaotic experience. Using the [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle's[/b][/color] exclusive custom [color=#00ffff][b]Predict[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]Condemn[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]spells[/b][/color] you may trigger several new [color=#ffff00][b]floor enchantment[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]offering[/b][/color] effects inside the dungeon.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]New Content[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] is now available to craft using the newly added [color=#ffff00][b]crafting material[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#00ff00]Oracle[/color][/b] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] provides up to [color=#00ffff][b]five set bonus effects[/b][/color], though unlike other class gear it [u]requires all five pieces to be equipped[/u]!
● [u]Seven new[/u][color=#ffff00][b] floor enchantments[/b][/color] and [u]four new[/u] [color=#ffff00][b]offering effects[/b][/color] have been added, all of which by default are unique to the [color=#00ffff][b]Oracle[/b][/color] class (and may be optionally enabled otherwise using a new [color=#00ffff][b]experimental configuration option[/b][/color]). These new additions bring the total number of possible combinations for various [color=#ffff00][b]effects[/b][/color] on a floor to [u]2,520[/u]!
● An additional [color=#ff7700][b]floor trap[/b][/color] has been added, the [color=#ff7700][b]Void Trap[/b][/color]. This trap creates a [color=#00ffff][b]giant donut shaped AOE[/b][/color] that [color=#ffff00][b]deals damage to you[/b][/color] while inside the void!
● Two new [color=#ffff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color] have been added, the [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Sight[/b][/color] and [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Intuition[/b][/color]. The [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Sight[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]reveals[/b][/color] all [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] on the current floor and [color=#ffff00][b]illuminates[/b][/color] dark dungeon floors. The [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Intuition[/b][/color] spawns a [color=#00ffff][b]treasure spot[/b][/color] a randomized number of floors down.
● A new mechanic, [color=#00ffff][b]hidden treasure spots[/b][/color], have been added that may only be found using the new [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Intuition[/b][/color]. When revealed, these spots [color=#ffff00][b]appear as yellow circles[/b][/color] on the ground, and may be claimed by moving into close proximity to them. Each [color=#00ff00][b]biome[/b][/color] has its own [color=#00ffff][b]treasure spot[/b][/color] rewards, featuring one of the five new [color=#ffff00][b]Lost Scroll[/b][/color] items!
● Five entirely new [color=#ffff00][b]Lost Scroll[/b][/color] items, which may [u]only[/u] be obtained from [color=#00ffff][b]treasure spots[/b][/color], have been added. These items offer [color=#00ff00][b]incredibly powerful beneficial effects[/b][/color] and may [u]even be used[/u] during [color=#ff7700][b]Item Penalty[/b][/color]! However, only one [color=#ffff00][b]Lost Scroll[/b][/color] item may be used per floor.
● The in-game [color=#00ffff][b]emoji icons[/b][/color] will now be displayed [u]above the player[/u] when [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] are activated to help convey when an effect has been triggered.
● Two new [color=#ffff00][b]special items[/b][/color] have been added to the [b][color=#00ffff]Blacksmith's Store[/color][/b] alongside the existing [color=#00ff00][b]mistpool equipment[/b][/color]. These items are [color=#ffff00][b]bag upgrades[/b][/color] and are intended for [u]new save files[/u] to easily upgrade their inventory due to sheer number of custom items introduced in the Deep Dungeon.
● A new [color=#00ffff][b]custom conversation[/b][/color] has been added with the [color=#ffff00][b]Caldarus Statue[/b][/color], allowing you to [u]teleport directly to the mines once per day[/u]. This option will only be available after the dungeon has been unlocked. Some story events may temporarily disable this option.[/size][/left]

[center][size=4][b][i]System Changes[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#ffff00][b]Keys[/b][/color] now exist for [u]every[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]lift room[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color], are now [u]craftable at any kitchen[/u], and their [color=#00ffff][b]recipes[/b][/color] are automatically unlocked upon reaching a [color=#00ffff][b]lift room[/b][/color] or [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color].
● [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Concealment[/b][/color] has been updated to help apply in some cases where monsters refuse to drop aggro. [color=#ff7700][b]Tome[/b][/color], [color=#ff7700][b]Griffin Statue[/b][/color], and [color=#ff7700][b]Void Cat[/b][/color] monsters will now be [u]rooted in place[/u] during [color=#ffff00][b]concealment[/b][/color], and [color=#ff7700][b]Purple Spirits[/b][/color] will be [u]deactivated entirely[/u] during [color=#ffff00][b]concealment[/b][/color].
● [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil of Alteration[/b][/color] has been redesigned. It now causes all monsters on the next floor to become the [u]same type[/u] of monster.
● The occurrence rate of the [b][color=#ffff00]Gloom[/color][/b] and [color=#ffff00][b]Fey[/b][/color] floor enchantments has been reduced by 10% [u]across all biomes[/u].
● [color=#ff7700][b]Gaze[/b][/color] traps have had been slightly nerfed, and now do 40% of your maximum health as damage by default.
● [color=#ff7700][b]Shroom[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] have been [u]slightly nerfed[/u], requiring slightly more time to pass before attacking after leaving stealth.
● All [color=#00ff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]recipes[/b][/color] have had their [color=#00ff00][b]biome specific[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]material requirements[/b][/color] reduced by 50%.
● Two new [color=#00ffff][b]configuration options[/b][/color] for controlling the power of the [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] have been added.
● Three new [color=#00ffff][b]configuration options[/b][/color] for controlling the power of the [color=#ff7700][b]Gloom[/b][/color] floor enchantment have been added.
● The previous [color=#00ffff][b]salve limit configuration option[/b][/color] has been separated into three individual options for each salve type.
● A new [color=#00ffff][b]experimental configuration option[/b][/color] has been added to enable the new [color=#ffff00][b]floor enchantments[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]offering effects[/b][/color] that are normally exclusive to the [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle[/b][/color] class. This is entirely for optional fun.
● A new [color=#00ffff][b]experimental configuration option[/b][/color] has been added to [u]adjust maximum health[/u] when entering a floor based on the [color=#00ff00][b]biome[/b][/color]. This is to help those who have "lost" maximum health due to a bug easily recover it.
● The [color=#00ffff][b]priestess portrait[/b][/color] has been updated, compliments of [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/profile/KathulhuArt]Kathulhu[/url]﻿.
● Updates to the [color=#ffff00][b]optional files[/b][/color] for the mod to making additional [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that are [u]normally only craftable[/u] to [u]also be purchasable[/u] at the [color=#00ff00][b]Blacksmith's shop[/b][/color] for those not wanting to obtain them via the standard crafting progression route.[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Major Update: Version 0.9.0[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]fourth major update[/u] to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] has arrived! This update includes [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color], [color=#00ffff][b]system changes[/b][/color], and [color=#00ffff][b]bug fixes[/b][/color]!

[b][color=#ff7700]Danger Awaits[/color][/b]: Two new types of [u]interactive[/u] [b][color=#ff7700]floor traps[/color][/b] have been added to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. These traps are different from the existing ones and will require you to [u]position yourself[/u] properly to avoid them. Each are [color=#ffff00][b]configurable[/b][/color] using the newly added [color=#00ffff][b]trap configuration properties[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Meteor Traps[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#ff7700]Meteor Traps[/color][/b] will display a custom "pulsing" [b][color=#00ffff]circular AOE indicator[/color][/b] when triggered, along with the standard trap notification. The meteor will "fall" over the next [b][color=#ffff00]10[/color][/b] in-game minutes. After this hidden countdown timer expires, the meteor will "explode", dealing a [b][color=#ff7700]percentage of your maximum health as damage[/color][/b] based on [b][color=#ffff00]your proximity to the impact[/color][/b]. Additionally, there is a [b][color=#ff7700]lethal zone[/color][/b] nearby the impact, so [color=#00ff00][b]don't stay too close[/b][/color]![/size][/center]
[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/6G09mPo.gif[/img][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Gaze Traps[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#ff7700]Gaze Traps[/color][/b] will spawn a "searching" [b][color=#00ffff]dragon eye[/color][/b] when triggered, along with the standard trap notification. The dragon eye will "look around" over the next [b][color=#ffff00]10[/color][/b] in-game minutes. After this hidden countdown timer expires, you will suffer a [b][color=#ff7700]percentage of your maximum health as damage[/color][/b] based on [b][color=#ffff00]whether you were facing the trap[/color][/b] or not. Keep in mind that [u]the direction the trap itself is looking is irrelevant[/u]. Only [u]your facing direction[/u] is what matters! In short, [color=#00ff00][b]look away[/b][/color] from it![/size][/center]
[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/WxW3zLb.gif[/img][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]New Content[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● Full support for the [b][color=#ffff00]Ruins[/color][/b] biome has been added. This includes [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] and [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] variants for all monster types! See the section on dread beasts for more details!
● Two new [u]interactive[/u] [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] have been added, [b][color=#ff7700]Meteor Traps[/color][/b] and [b][color=#ff7700]Gaze Traps[/color][/b].
● The [color=#ffff00][b]Ruins[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]boss battle[/b][/color] has been implemented. Craft and use the new [color=#00ff00][b]Ruins Orb[/b][/color] to trigger it from the [color=#00ffff][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color].[/size][/left]

[center][size=4][b][i]System Changes[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● New [b][color=#00ffff]configuration options[/color][/b] have been added allowing you to [b][color=#ffff00]customize[/color][/b] [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color].
● The [color=#ffff00][b]default damage[/b][/color] for [color=#ff7700][b]Explosion Traps[/b][/color] has been reduced. You can further tune this in the [b][color=#00ffff]configuration file[/color][/b].
● The [b][color=#ffff00]gain[/color][/b] (loudness) for the [color=#ff7700][b]Explosion Trap[/b][/color] sound effect has been reduced.
● [b][color=#ff7700]Rock Clod[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have had some of their custom attack patterns adjusted to help reduce performance issues.
● [color=#ffff00][b]Distortion[/b][/color] should no longer try to apply more than once to the same attack. The miss chance during distortion itself remains unchanged.
● [color=#00ff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color] when crafted will no longer receive infusions, even if cooking perks are enabled.
● Increased the maximum number of [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] during [b][color=#ff00ff]peril[/color][/b] for all [color=#ffff00][b]lava caves[/b][/color] floors.
● Updated the list of [color=#00ffff][b]random music[/b][/color] to include new songs added in 0.15 and some songs that weren't included previously.
● Your "guide" throughout the Deep Dungeon has changed. It doesn't seem to be the [color=#00ffff][b]Priestess[/b][/color] from before...[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Rules of the Dungeon[/u][/b][/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]The Dungeon's Curse[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]All standard consumable [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]weapons[/b][/color], and [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color] are [u]prohibited[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. Only items [i]specific[/i] to the Deep Dungeon, such as [b][color=#00ff00]Sigils[/color][/b], [b][color=#00ff00]Salves[/color][/b], and the [b][color=#00ff00]Mistpool[/color][/b] equipment are permitted. Additionally, all [b][color=#00ffff]mining[/color][/b] and [b][color=#00ffff]combat perks[/color][/b] as well as [color=#00ffff][b]infusions[/b][/color] are [u]disabled[/u] in the Deep Dungeon, and [color=#00ffff][b]status effects[/b][/color] are [u]removed[/u] when descending floors. Lastly, and most painful, the [color=#00ffff][b]dungeon's lift[/b][/color] is [u]disabled[/u].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Salves[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]only[/u] [color=#00ff00][b]healing[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] allowed in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. The [color=#00ff00][b]health[/b][/color], [color=#00ff00][b]stamina[/b][/color], and [color=#00ff00][b]mana[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]salves[/b][/color] may only be used [u]once[/u] per floor and provide [u]immediate[/u] recovery. A special salve, the [color=#ffff00][b]sustaining potion[/b][/color], has [u]no[/u] restrictions on its use and provides a one-hour [color=#00ff00][b]restoration[/b][/color] buff.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Sigils[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Powerful [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] found only in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. These [u]single use scrolls[/u] are imbued with powerful [color=#00ff00][b]beneficial[/b][/color] effects that will help you survive![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Floor Enchantments[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Custom special [color=#00ffff][b]effects[/b][/color] for each floor that are [u]randomly[/u] assigned. These offer a range of [color=#00ff00][b]beneficial[/b][/color] and [b][color=#ff7700]detrimental[/color][/b] effects that will make every descent into the dungeon unique![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Offerings[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Special [color=#00ffff][b]events[/b][/color] that allow you to [b][color=#ff00ff]sacrifice[/color][/b] [color=#ffff00][b]health[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]stamina[/b][/color], or [color=#ffff00][b]mana[/b][/color] before proceeding to the next floor. Doing so will grant an exceptionally powerful [color=#00ff00][b]beneficial[/b][/color] [u]OR[/u] [color=#ff7700][b]detrimental[/b][/color] effect on the next floor.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Floor Traps[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Hidden [color=#ff00ff][b]tiles[/b][/color] in the dungeon floor that activate by [u]proximity[/u]. Each trap triggers a unique [b][color=#ff7700]detrimental[/color][/b] effect that will temporarily hinder your progress on the floor![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Dread Beasts[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Extremely [u]dangerous[/u] [color=#ff00ff][b]monsters[/b][/color] with significantly bolstered [color=#ffff00][b]stats[/b][/color] (HP, Attack, Defense) and unique [u]custom[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]attack patterns[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Mistpool Equipment[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [color=#ffff00][b]mistpool[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]sword[/b][/color], and [b][color=#ffff00]pickaxe[/color][/b] are the [u]only[/u] basic equipment that function in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]! Be sure to stop by the [color=#00ff00][b]Blacksmith's Shop[/b][/color] to [u]purchase[/u] them before venturing into the dungeon![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Keys[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Single use [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that allow you to descend immediately to the [color=#00ffff][b]dungeon floor[/b][/color] associated with the [color=#ffff00][b]key[/b][/color]. A separate [color=#ffff00][b]key[/b][/color] and [color=#00ff00][b]recipe[/b][/color] exist for every [b][color=#00ffff]lift room[/color][/b] and [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color]. These are your primary method for returning to the deeper floors of the dungeon.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Orbs[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Special [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that may be [u]crafted[/u] using new crafting materials from each [color=#00ff00][b]biome[/b][/color]. These allow you to trigger a [color=#00ffff][b]boss fight[/b][/color] for a chance to obtain [u]special[/u] [color=#ffff00][b]loot[/b][/color]![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Cursed Gear[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Cursed pieces of [color=#ffff00][b]equipment[/b][/color] that may only be used as a [u]crafting ingredient[/u] to craft special [color=#ffff00][b]class armor[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Soulstones[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Strange [color=#ffff00][b]stones[/b][/color] said to contain the [color=#00ffff][b]memories[/b][/color] of a fallen adventurer. These rare items may only be used to [u]craft[/u] special [color=#ffff00][b]class armor[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Class Armor[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Rare and powerful [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color] that may only be [u]crafted[/u] using cursed gear, soulstones, and other [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] materials. These armor sets provide unique [color=#00ffff][b]set bonus effects[/b][/color] the more pieces you equip![/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Salves[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
These [color=#00ff00][b]healing[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] are your primary means of [color=#00ff00][b]recovery[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. Keep in mind that the health, stamina, and mana [color=#ffff00][b]salves[/b][/color] may only be used [u]once[/u] per floor. You may [u]purchase[/u] them at the [color=#00ffff][b]Clinic[/b][/color] without restrictions.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/73cYgeB.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Sigils[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
These powerful single use [b][color=#ffff00]items[/color][/b] may only be found in [b][color=#00ffff]treasure chests[/color][/b] within the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/3tq56jt.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Floor Enchantments[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
These random [color=#00ffff][b]effects[/b][/color] occur on floors in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b] and will be stated to you at the [u]start[/u] of a floor. Keep in mind that they may be [color=#00ff00][b]beneficial[/b][/color] or [b][color=#ff7700]detrimental[/color][/b] in nature. Up to [u]three[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]floor enchantments[/b][/color] may be active on a floor. [/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/B7WG6q8.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/EsN9HCL.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Haste[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#ffff00][b]movement speed[/b][/color] is [color=#00ff00][b]increased[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/gnJtbeS.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Gravity[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [b][color=#ffff00]movement speed[/color][/b] is [color=#ff7700][b]decreased[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/VfxczG3.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Restoration[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You [color=#00ff00][b]restore health over time[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/rAPSHs7.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]HP Penalty[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#ff7700][b]maximum HP is reduced[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/m5Y8Us4.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Second Wind[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You [b][color=#00ff00]recover stamina over time[/color][/b] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/44PYuJl.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Exhaustion[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#ff7700][b]stamina usage is doubled[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/S2pY4xu.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Amnesia[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You are [color=#ff7700][b]unable to cast spells[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/S6iaIoG.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Damage Down[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [b][color=#ffff00]damage[/color][/b] is [color=#ff7700][b]decreased[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/CJMh5lG.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Distortion[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#ffff00][b]accuracy[/b][/color] is [color=#ff7700][b]reduced[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/XYLSyvz.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Item Penalty[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You are [color=#ff7700][b]unable to use most items[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/Ajv7KcD.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Fey[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You are granted the [b][color=#00ffff]Fairy[/color][/b] [color=#00ff00][b]status effect[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]spell costs[/b][/color] are [color=#00ff00][b]reduced by half[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/I4RqnBD.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Gloom[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]All [b][color=#ff7700]monsters are stronger[/color][/b] on the current dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][quote][b]Author's Note: Special Floor Enchantments[/b]

The following [b]floor enchantments[/b] will [u]only[/u] occur when the [b]Oracle's Predict spell[/b] has been cast, or the new [b]experimental configuration option[/b] has been enabled.[/quote][/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/60rf6qF.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Blink (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]All [color=#00ff00][b]monsters have a small chance to miss[/b][/color] and [b][color=#ffff00]graze you[/color][/b] when attacking.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/tm3pAfP.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Deep Wounds (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]After taking [color=#ffff00][b]damage[/b][/color], [color=#ff7700][b]you suffer additional damage over time[/b][/color]. This effect [color=#ffff00][b]pools[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/5UOUiFF.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Stoneskin (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You start the floor with a [color=#00ff00][b]temporary over-shield[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/J5Om2Oh.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Frailty (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Taking [color=#ffff00][b]damage[/b][/color] [color=#ff7700][b]increases your damage received[/b][/color]. This effect [color=#ffff00][b]stacks[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/vEzgsBd.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Phalanx (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]All [color=#ffff00][b]damage[/b][/color] you receive is [color=#00ff00][b]reduced[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/Q5dplGo.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Fumigate (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You suffer [color=#ff7700][b]continuous damage over time[/b][/color]. The [color=#00ffff][b]sustaining potion[/b][/color] item will [color=#00ff00][b]slightly out-heal[/b][/color] this effect.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/x3UphRu.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Grudge (Special)[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Slaying a monster causes all remaining [color=#ff7700][b]monsters to become stronger[/b][/color]. This effect [color=#ffff00][b]stacks[/b][/color].[/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Offerings[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
These [color=#00ffff][b]events[/b][/color] occur randomly when descending floors in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. When one triggers, you will be presented with a [u]choice[/u] to [b][color=#ff7700]sacrifice[/color] [/b][color=#ffff00][b]health[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]mana[/b][/color], or [color=#ffff00][b]stamina[/b][/color]. Completing the offering will grant a [color=#00ffff][b]unique effect[/b][/color] on the [u]next[/u] dungeon floor. Keep in mind that they may be [color=#00ff00][b]beneficial[/b][/color] or [b][color=#ff7700]detrimental[/color][/b] in nature. Up to [u]one[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]offering[/b][/color] may be active on a floor. [/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/Invkeim.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Reckoning[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [color=#00ff00][b]health[/b][/color] of [color=#ffff00][b]you[/b][/color] and all [color=#ff00ff][b]monsters[/b][/color] is [color=#ff7700][b]set to 1[/b][/color] at the start of the next dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/NPUhr13.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Leech[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#00ff00][b]attacks heal you[/b][/color] for a small amount on the next dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/jKF1P7K.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Peril[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]More [color=#00ffff][b]floor traps[/b][/color] spawn on the next dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/pY8Sl9W.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Inner Fire[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You automatically cast the [color=#ffff00][b]Fire Breath[/b][/color] spell for free at the start of the next dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/5m4Va6x.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Dread[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]An incredibly powerful [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beast monster[/b][/color] will spawn on the next dungeon floor.[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][quote][b]Author's Note: Special Offerings[/b]

The following [b]offering effects[/b] will [u]only[/u] occur when the [b]Oracle's Condemn spell[/b] has been cast, or the new [b]experimental configuration option[/b] has been enabled.[/quote][/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/8RbtPDe.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Outbreak[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Monsters will [color=#ff7700][b]become lesser dread beasts[/b][/color] over time.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/b6HHZjW.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Spirit Link[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Monsters all [color=#ff7700][b]share a single combined health pool[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/CpHeJ8v.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Spikes[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]A portion of [color=#ffff00][b]damage deal to monsters[/b][/color] is [color=#ff7700][b]dealt back to you[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/GXz10gG.png[/img]  [size=4][b][i]Reflect[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]A portion of [color=#ffff00][b]damage dealt to you[/b][/color] is [color=#00ff00][b]dealt back to the nearest monster[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/WC0fbxW.png[/img][/center]
[center][size=3]All active [color=#00ffff][b]floor enchantments[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]offerings[/b][/color] for the current dungeon floor will be shown in the [u]custom dungeon backplate UI[/u]. This UI widget will [u]update automatically[/u] if floor enchantments or offerings ever change.[/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Floor Traps[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, floor traps are implemented for [b]all biomes[/b].[/quote]
[color=#00ffff][b]Floor Traps[/b][/color] are [u]hidden tiles[/u] present on floors in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b] that [u]activate by proximity[/u] and [color=#ff7700][b]cause powerful detrimental effects[/b][/color] to briefly hinder your progress. There are [u]seven different kinds[/u] of [b][color=#00ffff]floor traps[/color][/b], and the average number of traps present on a floor increases the deeper you are. [/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/cjVS2m2.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Confusing[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]Your [color=#00ffff][b]directional movement[/b][/color] is [color=#ff7700][b]inverted[/b][/color] for a brief period.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Disorienting[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [color=#00ffff][b]game HUD[/b][/color] is [color=#ff7700][b]hidden[/b][/color] for a brief period.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Exploding[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#ffff00]You[/color][/b] and all [color=#ff00ff][b]monsters[/b][/color] nearby the trap take [color=#ff7700][b]significant damage[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Inhibiting[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]You are [color=#ff7700][b]unable to attack with weapons[/b][/color] for a brief period.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Luring[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][color=#ff00ff][b]Monsters[/b][/color] are [color=#ff7700][b]summoned nearby[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Meteor[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]A [color=#ff00ff][b]meteor[/b][/color] begins falling at the target location. After 10 in-game minutes it [color=#ffff00][b]explodes[/b][/color] dealing [color=#ff7700][b]damage based on your proximity[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Gaze[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]A [color=#ff00ff][b]dragon eye[/b][/color] appears at the target location. After 10 in-game minutes it [b][color=#ffff00]disappears[/color][/b], [color=#ff7700][b]damaging you if you were facing it[/b][/color] when it [b][color=#ffff00]vanished[/color][/b].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Void[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]A [color=#ff00ff][b]donut shaped AOE[/b][/color] appears at the target location. You will [color=#ff7700][b]suffer damage over time[/b][/color] while [color=#ffff00][b]inside the void[/b][/color].[/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Dread Beasts[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, dread beasts are implemented for the [b]all current monster types[/b] across [b]all biomes[/b].[/quote]
[b][color=#ff00ff]Dread Beasts[/color][/b] are [u]incredibly powerful[/u] monsters that may rarely appear in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. These monsters have [color=#ff7700][b]significantly increased stats[/b][/color] and use [color=#ff7700][b]custom attack patterns[/b][/color] to engage you. The formidable enemies pose a significant threat and should be approached with extreme caution. Defeating a [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] has a [u]chance[/u] to reward you with a rare [color=#ffff00][b]soulstone item [/b][/color]used for [u]crafting[/u] special [color=#ffff00][b]class equipment[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/NeCgjbq.gif[/img][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Clods[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][color=#00ffff][b]Clod[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] will [u]randomly select one of the three[/u] following [color=#ff7700][b]attack patterns[/b][/color] to continuously attack with: [b][color=#ffff00]Wall[/color][/b], [b][color=#ffff00]Spin[/color][/b], or [b][color=#ffff00]Split[/color][/b]. The [b][color=#ffff00]wall[/color][/b] pattern causes the clod to shoot a [color=#ff7700][b]large line of 10 pellets[/b][/color] repeatedly. The [color=#ffff00][b]spin[/b][/color] pattern causes the clod to [color=#ff7700][b]spin[/b][/color] while shooting pellets at [color=#ff7700][b]varying angles[/b][/color] repeatedly. The [color=#ffff00][b]split[/b][/color] pattern causes the clod to shoot a [color=#ff7700][b]barrage[/b][/color] of pellets that [color=#ff7700][b]continuously split[/b][/color] into more pellets.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Saplings[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][color=#00ffff][b]Sapling[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] have the [u]combined properties of all sapling variants[/u] in the game. They have significantly increased [color=#ff7700][b]jump[/b][/color] and [color=#ff7700][b]attack distances[/b][/color], extremely reduced [color=#ff7700][b]idle time[/b][/color] between attacks, drop a [color=#ff7700][b]slowing puddle[/b][/color] when landing, and even [color=#ff7700][b]split into three more saplings[/b][/color] when defeated! The [color=#00ffff][b]saplings[/b][/color] they split into are the same [u]variant[/u] as the [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beast[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Shrooms[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][color=#00ffff][b]Shroom[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] have the [u]combined properties of all shroom variants[/u] in the game. They have extremely increased [color=#ff7700][b]stealth[/b][/color] and [color=#ff7700][b]attack[/b][/color] speeds, and drop a [color=#ff7700][b]poison puddle[/b][/color] after attacking. Additionally, they will enter [color=#ff7700][b]stealth[/b][/color] immediately when the floor starts, and re-enter [color=#ff7700][b]stealth[/b][/color] if the player moves away without attacking.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Enchanterns[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Enchantern[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an extremely increased [color=#ff7700][b]dash distance[/b][/color] and the [color=#ff7700][b]balls of electricity[/b][/color] they drop [color=#ff7700][b]persist[/b][/color] for a significant amount of time.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Stalagmites[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][color=#00ffff][b]Stalagmite[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] will [u]randomly select one of the two[/u] following [color=#ff7700][b]attack patterns[/b][/color] to continuously attack with: [b][color=#ffff00]Circle[/color][/b] or [b][color=#ffff00]Cross[/color][/b]. Each pattern has two types of attacks the [b][color=#00ffff]stalagmite[/color][/b] will [u]alternate[/u] between using. Additionally, the type of attack initially used is randomly selected depending on the pattern. The [b][color=#ffff00]circle[/color][/b] pattern causes the stalagmite to alternate between creating a [color=#ff7700][b]large circle of spikes on top of itself [/b][/color]and an [color=#ff7700][b]enormous circle of spikes further away from itself[/b][/color]. The [color=#ffff00][b]cross[/b][/color] pattern causes the stalagmite to alternate between creating a [color=#ff7700][b]large cross of spikes on top of itself[/b][/color] in either [color=#ff7700][b]cardinal[/b][/color] or [color=#ff7700][b]inter-cardinal[/b][/color] directions.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Bats[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Bat[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have extremely increased [color=#ff7700][b]movement speed[/b][/color], will [color=#ff7700][b]more aggressively follow and attack[/b][/color] the player, and always shoot [color=#ff7700][b]three soundwaves[/b][/color] with every attack.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Cats[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Lava Cat[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an enormous [color=#ff7700][b]charge distance[/b][/color] and [color=#ff7700][b]significantly reduced idle time[/b][/color] between attacks. They are also [color=#ff7700][b]highly resistant to water[/b][/color] and will [color=#ff7700][b]shrug off the petrification effect[/b][/color] very quickly.[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Void Cat[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an enormous [color=#ff7700][b]charge distance[/b][/color] and [color=#ff7700][b]significantly reduced idle time[/b][/color] between attacks. They are also [color=#ff7700][b]immune to light[/b][/color] and will [color=#ff7700][b]ignore its effects[/b][/color] entirely.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Spirits[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Flame Spirit[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have significantly increased [color=#ff7700][b]teleportation speed[/b][/color] and the [color=#ff7700][b]balls of fire[/b][/color] they shoot [color=#ff7700][b]persist[/b][/color] for a significant amount of time, allowing up to [color=#ff7700][b]two fireballs[/b][/color] to seek the player simultaneously.[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Purple Spirit[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have significantly increased [color=#ff7700][b]teleportation speed[/b][/color] and [b][color=#ff7700]attack speed[/color][/b], and the [color=#ff7700][b]ring of fire[/b][/color] they create [color=#ff7700][b]is much closer[/b][/color] to them, creating a [color=#ff7700][b]smaller safe zone[/b][/color] to attack them in.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Tomes[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Tome[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an extremely increased [b][color=#ff7700]attack radius[/color][/b] and [color=#ff7700][b]movement speed[/b][/color], will [color=#ff7700][b]more aggressively follow and attack[/b][/color] the player, and always shoot [color=#ff7700][b]three soundwaves[/b][/color] with every attack.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Rock Stacks[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Rock Stack[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an extremely increased [color=#ff7700][b]attack radius[/b][/color], will [color=#ff7700][b]recombine instantly at any distance after attacking[/b][/color] the player, and will [color=#ff7700][b]perfectly follow the player[/b][/color] with every attack up until the last second.[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]Statues[/i][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3][b][color=#00ffff]Griffin Statue[/color][/b] [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beasts[/color][/b] have an increased [color=#ff7700][b]movement speed[/b][/color], will [color=#ff7700][b]more aggressively follow and attack[/b][/color] the player, and will [color=#ff7700][b]recoil less[/b][/color] after being attacked.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/LNIXRKy.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=3]You will [u]always be notified[/u] if a [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] is present on a dungeon floor at the [u]start of a floor[/u]. Use that knowledge to prepare accordingly and survive.[/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Mistpool Equipment[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
The [color=#00ffff][b]Mistpool[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]weapon[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color], and [color=#ffff00][b]pickaxe[/b][/color] are the [u]only[/u] standard equipment permitted in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. These pieces of equipment have a [color=#00ffff][b]unique effect[/b][/color] where they [color=#00ff00][b]increase in power[/b][/color] the [u]deeper in the dungeon you are[/u]. To explain further, the [color=#ffff00][b]mistpool sword's[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]attack value[/b][/color] will [color=#00ff00][b]increase[/b][/color] the [u]higher the floor number[/u], and the same is true for the [color=#ffff00][b]mistpool armor's[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]defense[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]value[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#ffff00]mistpool pickaxe's[/color][/b] [color=#00ffff][b]damage[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]charge level[/b][/color] will also [b][color=#00ff00]increase[/color][/b] the [u]higher the floor number[/u].[/size][/center]

[center][size=3]Additionally, the [b][color=#ffff00]mistpool equipment[/color][/b] has [u]custom sprites and assets[/u] that [color=#00ffff][b]glow brighter[/b][/color] as their [color=#00ff00][b]power increases[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/hgBwR4N.png[/img][/center][center][img]https://i.imgur.com/GVsFkpL.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=3]Make sure to purchase the [color=#ffff00][b]mistpool equipment[/b][/color] at the [color=#00ffff][b]Blacksmith's Shop[/b][/color] [u]before entering[/u] the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]![/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Keys[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, keys are [b]craftable[/b] and implemented for [b]all biomes[/b].[/quote]
[color=#ffff00][b]Keys[/b][/color] are single use [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that may be used to [u]descend[/u] to a [b][color=#00ffff]lift room[/color][/b] or [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] from the [color=#00ffff][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color], effectively allowing you to [u]circumvent the locked lift[/u]. [color=#ffff00][b]Keys[/b][/color] may be [u]crafted at any kitchen[/u] using [color=#00ff00][b]biome specific[/b][/color] [b][color=#ffff00]materials[/color][/b], and the [color=#ffff00][b]recipes[/b][/color] are [u]automatically unlocked[/u] upon reaching the key's required [color=#00ffff][b]floor[/b][/color]. [color=#ffff00][b]Keys[/b][/color] are also awarded to you for reaching a [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color] [u]without the use[/u] of a [color=#ffff00][b]key[/b][/color]. Additionally, all [color=#ff7700][b]monsters[/b][/color] have a [u]very low chance[/u] of dropping a [color=#ffff00][b]key [/b][/color]when defeated.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/QPbpi0p.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Orbs[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, orbs are implemented for [b]all biomes [/b][u]after[/u] the [b]Upper Mines[/b].[/quote]
[color=#ffff00][b]Orbs[/b][/color] are single use [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that may be used to [u]initiate[/u] a [color=#00ffff][b]boss battle[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] from the [color=#00ffff][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color]. [b][color=#ffff00]Orbs[/color][/b] may be [u]crafted at any kitchen[/u] using unique [color=#ffff00][b]materials[/b][/color] gathered in the various [color=#00ff00][b]biomes[/b][/color] within the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. A separate [color=#ffff00][b]orb[/b][/color] exists for each [color=#00ff00][b]biome[/b][/color] other than the [b][color=#00ff00]Upper Mines[/color][/b].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/odrIkRx.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=3][color=#00ffff][b]Boss battles[/b][/color] take place in a special [color=#ff00ff][b]arena[/b][/color] where [color=#ffff00][b]sigils[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]spells[/b][/color] are [u]prohibited[/u]. The [color=#00ff00][b]victory condition[/b][/color] is to simply [u]defeat all boss monsters[/u], and doing so will [u]always[/u] reward you with a rare [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone item[/b] [/color]used for [u]crafting[/u] special [color=#ffff00][b]class equipment[/b][/color].[/size][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Cursed Gear[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, the cursed gear associated with [b]all biomes[/b] has been implemented.[/quote]
[color=#ffff00][b]Cursed gear[/b][/color] is [u]crafting material[/u] found in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. It can [u]rarely[/u] be found in [color=#00ffff][b]treasure chests[/b][/color] and is a [u]guaranteed[/u] reward for reaching a [color=#00ffff][b]seal room[/b][/color] [u]without[/u] the use of a [color=#ffff00][b]key[/b][/color]. Crafting [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] [u]requires[/u] a piece of [color=#ffff00][b]cursed gear[/b][/color] matching the same equipment slot.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/JJTXp6P.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Soul Stones[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, the [b]Cleric[/b], [b]Dark Knight[/b], [b]Mage[/b], [b]Paladin[/b], [b]Rogue[/b], and [b]Oracle [/b]soul stones are implemented.[/quote]
[color=#ffff00][b]Soul stones[/b][/color] are another [u]crafting material[/u] found in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]. They can [u]sometimes[/u] be obtained by defeating a [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beast[/b][/color], and are also a [u]guaranteed[/u] reward for completing a [color=#00ffff][b]boss battle[/b][/color]. [color=#ffff00][b]Soul stones[/b][/color] are associated with a [color=#00ff00][b]class[/b][/color] and may [u]only[/u] be used to craft the gear specific to that class. For example, the [color=#00ff00][b]cleric[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color] may [u]only[/u] be used for crafting [color=#00ff00][b]cleric[/b][/color] gear.[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/Lz5lrEh.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Item Exchange[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[color=#00ffff][b]Interacting[/b][/color] ("speaking") with the [b][color=#00ffff]dragon statue[/color][/b] in the [color=#00ff00][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color] is used to trigger the [color=#00ffff][b]item exchange[/b][/color] feature. Using this, you may [color=#00ffff][b]exchange[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stones[/b][/color] or [color=#ffff00][b]cursed armor[/b][/color] [u]in your inventory[/u] for the special [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil Parchment[/b][/color] item, which is [u]used to craft[/u] [color=#ffff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color]![/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/gT9e9RH.gif[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Crafting Sigils[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/JN6H1XT.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=3]While the primary source of [color=#00ff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color] are [color=#00ffff][b]treasure chests[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color], it is possible to [u]craft them[/u] at any [color=#00ffff][b]kitchen[/b][/color] using the special [color=#ffff00][b]Sigil Parchment[/b][/color] item obtained from the [color=#00ffff][b]item exchange[/b][/color] described above. The [color=#ffff00][b]recipe[/b][/color] for every [color=#ffff00][b]Sigil[/b][/color] is available by [u]default[/u], and each recipe only requires [u]one[/u] [color=#ffff00][b]Sigil Parchment[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=3][quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
The item icons in the crafting menu for Sigils will show their disabled icons. This is because they are currently unusable, as you are not in the Deep Dungeon while crafting. It has no affect on whether you may craft the item or not.[/quote][/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/TOMyPAE.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b][u]Class Armor[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
[quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
As of Deep Dungeon v1.0, the [b]Cleric[/b], [b]Dark Knight[/b], [b]Mage[/b], [b]Paladin[/b], [b]Rogue[/b], and [b]Oracle[/b] class gear is implemented.[/quote]
[color=#ffff00][b]Class armor[/b][/color] are [u]legendary[/u] pieces of [color=#ffff00][b]equipment[/b][/color] that must be [u]crafted[/u] using [color=#ffff00][b]materials[/b][/color] from the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This special armor provides [color=#00ffff][b]unique set bonuses[/b][/color] the more pieces from a [u]matching set[/u] you equip [u]simultaneously[/u]. Obtaining all of the [color=#ffff00][b]materials[/b][/color] to craft these powerful armor sets will require you to travel to deepest floors of the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/3ygcYEV.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/zOwX4KR.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/AcEf2UY.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/p4EeTkL.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/RgSwbZN.png[/img][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/8McVLBG.png[/img][/center]

[center][size=3]The [color=#ffff00][b]class armor[/b][/color] recipes will be [u]unlocked automatically[/u] and are available in the [color=#00ffff][b]blacksmithing crafting menu[/b][/color]. Each piece of armor in the set will require crafting [color=#ffff00][b]materials[/b][/color] from a specific [color=#00ff00][b]biome[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color], in addition to a [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/UKxKy1l.png[/img][/center]


[center][size=6][b]Configuration[/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The mod is [u]customizable[/u] and allows you to configure various aspects of the mod. The list below contains details for each [color=#ffff00][b]configuration option[/b][/color].[/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [b][color=#ffff00]Disable Dungeon Lift[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if the [color=#00ffff][b]dungeon lift[/b][/color] is [u]disabled[/u]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [b][color=#ffff00]Randomize Dungeon Music[/color][/b]: A [b][color=#00ff00]boolean[/color][/b] value that controls if [color=#00ffff][b]music[/b][/color] is [u]randomized each floor[/u]. This property must be set to either [b][color=#00ff00]true[/color][/b] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [b][color=#ffff00]Restrict Items[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if most [color=#00ffff][b]items[/b][/color] ([u]excluding[/u] [b][color=#00ffff]Sigils[/color][/b] and [b][color=#00ffff]Salves[/color][/b]) are [u]restricted[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [color=#ffff00][b]Restrict Armor[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if most [color=#00ffff][b]armor[/b][/color] (excluding [b][color=#00ffff]Mistpool[/color][/b] and [b][color=#00ffff]Class[/color][/b] equipment) is [u]restricted[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [color=#ffff00][b]Restrict Tools[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if most [color=#00ffff][b]tools[/b][/color] (excluding the [b][color=#00ffff]Mistpool[/color][/b] pickaxe) are [u]restricted[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [color=#ffff00][b]Restrict Weapons[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if most [color=#00ffff][b]weapons[/b][/color] (excluding the [b][color=#00ffff]Mistpool[/color][/b] sword) are [u]restricted[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [color=#ffff00][b]Restrict Perks[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if most [color=#00ffff][b]perks[/b][/color] (specifically [u]mining and combat[/u]) are [u]restricted[/u] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [color=#ffff00][b]Health Salve Limit[/b][/color]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls [u]how many[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]health salves[/b][/color] may be used per floor. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]999[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Stamina Salve Limit[/b][/color]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls [u]how many[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]stamina salves[/b][/color] may be used per floor. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]999[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Mana Salve Limit[/b][/color]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls [u]how many[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]mana salves[/b][/color] may be used per floor. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]999[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Health Salve Potency[/color][/b]: An [b][color=#00ff00]integer[/color][/b] value that controls the [u]amount[/u] of [color=#00ffff][b]health[/b][/color] restored by the [b][color=#00ffff]salve[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]999[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Stamina Salve Potency[/color][/b]: An [b][color=#00ff00]integer[/color][/b] value that controls the [u]amount[/u] of [color=#00ffff][b]stamina[/b][/color] restored by the [b][color=#00ffff]salve[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]999[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Mana Salve Potency[/color][/b]: An [b][color=#00ff00]integer[/color][/b] value that controls the [u]amount[/u] of [color=#00ffff][b]mana[/b][/color] restored by the [b][color=#00ffff]salve[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]1[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]999[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Sustaining Potion Duration Modifier[/color][/b]: A [b][color=#00ff00]decimal[/color][/b] value that acts as a [u]multiplier[/u] to the [u]duration[/u] of the [b][color=#ffff00]sustaining potion[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]0.5[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]2.0[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Random Dread Beast Spawn Chance[/color][/b]: An [b][color=#00ff00]integer[/color][/b] value that controls the [u]probability[/u] of a [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] [u]spawning at the start of a floor[/u]. This effect may NOT occur if an [b][color=#00ffff]offering[/color][/b] is [u]already active[/u] at the start of a floor. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]100[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Offering Event Chance[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [u]probability[/u] of an [b][color=#00ffff]offering event[/color][/b] occurring when [u]descending to the next floor[/u]. This effect may NOT occur on the [u]last floor of a biome[/u]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]100[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Offering Health Requirement[/color][/b]: An [b][color=#00ff00]integer[/color][/b] value that controls the amount of [color=#00ffff][b]health[/b][/color] [u]required[/u], if selected, for an [color=#00ffff][b]offering event[/b][/color]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]90[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Offering Stamina Requirement[/b][/color]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the amount of [color=#00ffff][b]stamina[/b][/color] [u]required[/u], if selected, for an [color=#00ffff][b]offering event[/b][/color]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]90[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Offering Mana Requirement[/b][/color]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the amount of [color=#00ffff][b]mana[/b][/color] [u]required[/u], if selected, for an [color=#00ffff][b]offering event[/b][/color]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]16[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Dread Beast Damage Modifier[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the [u]multiplier[/u] used for [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beast[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]damage[/b][/color]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]1.0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]2.0[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Dread Beast Health Modifier[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the multiplier used for [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] [b][color=#00ffff]health[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]1.0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]3.0[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Gloom Monster Damage Dealt Modifier[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the multiplier used for [b][color=#ff00ff]gloom monster[/color][/b] [b][color=#00ffff]damage dealt[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]1.0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]1.5[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Gloom Monster Damage Received Modifier[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the multiplier used for [b][color=#ff00ff]gloom monster[/color][/b] [b][color=#00ffff]damage received[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0.5[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]1.0[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [color=#ffff00][b]Gloom Monster Health Modifier[/b][/color]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the multiplier used for [b][color=#ff00ff]gloom monster[/color][/b] [b][color=#00ffff]health[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]1.0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]1.5[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Cursed Armor Drop Chance Modifier[/color][/b]: A [b][color=#00ff00]decimal[/color][/b] value that acts as a [u]multiplier[/u] to the [u]probability[/u] that [color=#00ffff][b]cursed armor[/b][/color] will drop from [b][color=#00ffff]treasure chests[/color][/b]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1.0[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]10.0[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Soul Stone Drop Chance[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [u]probability[/u] of a [color=#00ffff][b]soul stone[/b][/color] dropping when a [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] is defeated. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]100[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Lift Key Drop Chance[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [u]probability[/u] of a [color=#00ffff][b]lift key[/b][/color] dropping when a [color=#ff00ff][b]monster[/b][/color] is defeated. This effect may NOT occur in the Upper Mines biome. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]100[/b][/color] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Enable Boss Fight Restrictions[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if [color=#00ffff][b]boss battles[/b][/color] should have [color=#00ffff][b]sigils[/b][/color] and [b][color=#00ffff]spells[/color][/b] [u]disabled[/u]. This property must be set to either [color=#00ff00][b]true[/b][/color] or [color=#00ff00][b]false[/b][/color].
● [b][color=#ffff00]Confusing Trap Duration Seconds[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]duration of confusing traps[/b][/color]. The value is specified in [u]seconds[/u]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]1200[/b][/color] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Disorienting Trap Duration Seconds[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]duration of disorienting traps[/b][/color]. The value is specified in [u]seconds[/u]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]600[/b][/color] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Inhibiting Trap Duration Seconds[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]duration of inhibiting traps[/b][/color]. The value is specified in [u]seconds[/u]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]900[/b][/color] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Exploding Trap Current Health Damage Percent[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]percentage of your current health[/b][/color] you will take as damage. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]80[/b][/color] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Luring Trap Monster Spawn Count[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]numbers of monsters[/b][/color] that will spawn. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]2[/color][/b] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Gaze Trap Max Health Damage Percent[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]percentage of your max health[/b][/color] you will take as damage. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]99[/color][/b] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Meteor Trap Scaling Factor[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]decimal[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]damage scaling[/b][/color] applied to meteors. Lower values, with the exception of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b], [u]increase[/u] the amount of damage taken by proximity. This property must be set to one of the following values: [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b], [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b], [b][color=#00ff00]1.5[/color][/b], [b][color=#00ff00]2[/color][/b], [b][color=#00ff00]2.5[/color][/b], or [b][color=#00ff00]3[/color][/b]. A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Void Trap Duration Seconds[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]duration of void traps[/b][/color]. The value is specified in [u]seconds[/u]. This property must be set to a value within the range of [color=#00ff00][b]0[/b][/color] to [color=#00ff00][b]1800[/b][/color] (inclusive). A value of [b][color=#00ff00]0[/color][/b] effectively [u]disables[/u] the trap.
● [b][color=#ffff00]Mistpool Equipment Store Price[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]purchase price[/b][/color] of all [color=#00ffff][b]mistpool equipment[/b][/color] at the Blacksmith's store. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]500[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Salves Store Price[/color][/b]: An [color=#00ff00][b]integer[/b][/color] value that controls the [color=#00ffff][b]purchase price[/b][/color] of all [color=#00ffff][b]salves[/b][/color] at the Clinic's store. This property must be set to a value within the range of [b][color=#00ff00]1[/color][/b] to [b][color=#00ff00]50[/color][/b] (inclusive).
● [b][color=#ffff00]Experimental Extra Floor Enchantments and Offerings[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if the new [color=#00ffff][b]floor enchantments[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]offering[/b][/color] effects can be encountered [u]without[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]Oracle[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]spells[/b][/color]. This property must be set to either [b][color=#00ff00]true[/color][/b] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
● [b][color=#ffff00]Experimental Max Health Bug Fix[/color][/b]: A [color=#00ff00][b]boolean[/b][/color] value that controls if your [color=#00ffff][b]maximum health[/b][/color] should be adjusted when entering a dungeon floor. This is to help correct any maximum health "lost" due to bugs. This property must be set to either [b][color=#00ff00]true[/color][/b] or [b][color=#00ff00]false[/color][/b].
[/size][/left]

[center][size=3][quote][b]Author's Note[/b]:
The [u]configuration file[/u] will NOT exist until the game (and mod) have been started [u]at least once[/u]. Therefore, if you wish to configure the mod, start the game until the title screen loads, then EXIT the game, and lastly edit the configuration file before restarting the game.[/quote]
In order to [b]customize[/b] the mod, you must modify the properties in its [u]configuration file[/u]. This file is located in the [b]mod_data[/b] folder inside the [b]Fields of Mistria[/b] folder where the [u]game is located[/u]. Below is a directory tree view of where the [u]configuration file[/u] exists beginning with the folder that the game is in:
[/size][/center]
[code]Fields of Mistria
├─ FieldsOfMistria.exe
├─ mod_data
│  ├─ DeepDungeon
│  │  ├─ DeepDungeon.json
[/code]

[center][size=3]The full "path" to the file will vary depending on [u]where the game is installed[/u]. For example, with the game installed via [b]Steam[/b] on the [b]C[/b] drive the full path for the [u]configuration file[/u] would be:[/size][/center]
[code]C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\Fields of Mistria\mod_data\DeepDungeon\DeepDungeon.json
[/code]

[center][size=3]The [b]configuration file[/b] by [u]default[/u] will look like the following:[/size][/center]
[code]﻿{
    "confusing_trap_duration_seconds": 1200,
    "cursed_armor_drop_chance_modifier": 1.0,
    "disable_dungeon_lift": true,
    "disorienting_trap_duration_seconds": 600,
    "dread_beast_damage_modifier": 2.0,
    "dread_beast_health_modifier": 3.0,
    "enable_boss_fight_restrictions": true,
    "experimental_extra_floor_enchantments_and_offerings": false,
    "experimental_max_health_bug_fix": false,
    "exploding_trap_current_health_damage_percent": 50,
    "gaze_trap_max_health_damage_percent": 40,
    "gloom_monster_damage_dealt_modifier": 1.5,
    "gloom_monster_damage_received_modifier": 0.5,
    "gloom_monster_health_modifier": 1.5,
    "health_salve_limit": 3,
    "health_salve_potency": 35,
    "inhibiting_trap_duration_seconds": 900,
    "lift_key_drop_chance": 2,
    "luring_trap_monster_spawn_count": 2,
    "mana_salve_limit": 1,
    "mana_salve_potency": 1,
    "meteor_trap_scaling_factor": 2.5,
    "mistpool_equipment_store_price": 500,
    "offering_event_chance": 15,
    "offering_health_requirement": 25,
    "offering_mana_requirement": 1,
    "offering_stamina_requirement": 20,
    "random_dread_beast_spawn_chance": 5,
    "randomize_dungeon_music": true,
    "restrict_armor": true,
    "restrict_items": true,
    "restrict_perks": true,
    "restrict_tools": true,
    "restrict_weapons": true,
    "salves_store_price": 50,
    "soul_stone_drop_chance": 35,
    "stamina_salve_limit": 3,
    "stamina_salve_potency": 35,
    "sustaining_potion_duration_modifier": 0.5,
    "void_trap_duration_seconds": 1200
}
[/code]


[center][size=6][b][u]Major Update: Version 0.8.0[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]third major update[/u] to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] has arrived! This update includes [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color], [color=#00ffff][b]system changes[/b][/color], and [color=#00ffff][b]bug fixes[/b][/color]!

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/udHbD91.png[/img][/center]

[color=#00ffff][b]Adventurer's Spirit[/b][/color]: Obtain the new [b][color=#00ff00]Paladin[/color][/b] and [b][color=#00ff00]Rogue[/color][/b] [b][color=#ffff00]class gear[/color][/b] to help you conquer the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]New Content[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ff00][b]Paladin[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] is now available to craft using the newly added [color=#ffff00][b]crafting material[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Paladin[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#00ff00]Paladin[/color][/b] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] provides up to [color=#00ffff][b]three set bonus effects[/b][/color], with the first effect [u]increasing in power[/u] when up to three or five pieces are equipped!
● [color=#00ff00][b]Rogue[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] is now available to craft using the newly added [color=#ffff00][b]crafting material[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Rogue[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#00ff00]Rogue[/color][/b] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] provides up to [color=#00ffff][b]five set bonus effects[/b][/color], with [u]each piece equipped[/u] unlocking a new effect![/size][/left]

[center][size=4][b][i]System Changes[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● A new [color=#00ffff][b]configuration option[/b][/color] was added to [color=#00ffff][b]control if perks are disabled[/b][/color] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color].
● [color=#00ff00][b]Sigils of Redemption[/b][/color] and [color=#00ff00][b]Protection[/b][/color] may now be [u]used more than once per floor[/u], provided their respective [color=#00ffff][b]status effects[/b][/color] are [u]not currently active[/u].
● [color=#ff7700][b]Sapling[/b][/color] [color=#ff00ff][b]dread beasts[/b][/color] are now [u]significantly more aggressive[/u].
● Updates to the [color=#ffff00][b]optional files[/b][/color] for the mod to making additional [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that are [u]normally only craftable[/u] to [u]also be purchasable[/u] at the [color=#00ff00][b]Blacksmith's shop[/b][/color] for those not wanting to obtain them via the standard crafting progression route.[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Major Update: Version 0.7.0[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]second major update[/u] to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] has arrived! This update includes [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color], [color=#00ffff][b]system changes[/b][/color], and [color=#00ffff][b]bug fixes[/b][/color]!

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/V5auiyh.gif[/img][/center]

One piece of [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color] is the addition of the [color=#ffff00][b]Lava Caves Boss Battle[/b][/color]. Craft and use the newly added [color=#00ff00][b]Lava Caves Orb[/b][/color] at the [u]mines entrance to initiate it[/u].[/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]New Content[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ff00][b]Mage[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] is now available to craft using the newly added [color=#ffff00][b]crafting material[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Mage[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#00ff00]Mage[/color][/b] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] provides up to [color=#00ffff][b]five set bonus effects[/b][/color], with each piece worn unlocking an effect! These [color=#00ffff][b]effects[/b][/color] revolve entirely around [color=#00ffff][b]spell casting[/b][/color], including adding [u]three new spells[/u] that are [u]only available[/u] in the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color]!
● [color=#00ffff][b]Floor Traps[/b][/color] have been added for the [color=#00ff00][b]Lava Caves[/b][/color] biome.
● [color=#ff00ff][b]Dread Beast[/b][/color] implementations added for [color=#ff00ff][b]Bat[/b][/color], [color=#ff00ff][b]Lava Cat[/b][/color], and [color=#ff00ff][b]Flame Spirit[/b][/color] monsters.
● The [color=#00ff00][b]Lava Caves[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]boss battle[/b][/color] has been added, [u]craft and use[/u] the [color=#ffff00][b]Lava Caves Orb[/b][/color] to initiate it at the [color=#00ff00][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color].[/size][/left]

[center][size=4][b][i]System Changes[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ffff][b]Interacting[/b][/color] ("speaking") with the [b][color=#00ffff]dragon statue[/color][/b] in the [color=#00ff00][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color] is now used to trigger the [color=#00ffff][b]item exchange[/b][/color] feature. Using this, you may exchange [color=#ffff00][b]soul stones[/b][/color] or [color=#ffff00][b]cursed armor[/b][/color] [u]in your inventory[/u] for the new [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil Parchment[/b][/color] item, [u]used to craft[/u] [color=#ffff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color]!
● [color=#ffff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color] may now be [u]crafted at any kitchen[/u], but [u]require[/u] the newly added special [color=#00ff00][b]Sigil Parchment[/b][/color] item to do so.
● Updates to the [color=#ffff00][b]optional files[/b][/color] for the mod to making additional [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that are [u]normally only craftable[/u] to [u]also be purchasable[/u] at the [color=#00ff00][b]Blacksmith's shop[/b][/color] for those not wanting to obtain them via the standard crafting progression route.[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Major Update: Version 0.6.0[/u][/b][/size][/center]
[center][size=3]The [u]first major update[/u] to the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] has arrived! This update includes [color=#00ffff][b]new content[/b][/color], [color=#00ffff][b]system changes[/b][/color], [u]optional[/u] [color=#00ffff][b]mod add-on files[/b][/color], and [color=#00ffff][b]bug fixes[/b][/color]!

[center][img]https://i.imgur.com/43E917s.png[/img][/center]

One major [color=#00ffff][b]system change[/b][/color] is the introduction of a [color=#ffff00][b]mod configuration file[/b][/color]. This file allows you [u]customize[/u] several aspects of the mod, such as whether the [color=#00ff00][b]dungeon lift[/b][/color] is [u]disabled or not[/u]. See the [b]Configuration[/b] section for more information![/size][/center]

[center][size=4][b][i]New Content[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ff00][b]Dark Knight[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] is now available to craft. Requires the newly added [color=#ffff00][b]crafting material[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Dark Knight[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]soul stone[/b][/color].
● [color=#00ffff][b]Floor Traps[/b][/color] have been added for the [color=#00ff00][b]Deep Earth[/b][/color] biome.
● [color=#ff00ff][b]Dread Beast[/b][/color] implementations added for [color=#ff00ff][b]Shroom[/b][/color], [color=#ff00ff][b]Sapling[/b][/color], an [color=#ff00ff][b]Enchantern[/b][/color] monsters.
● The [color=#00ff00][b]Deep Earth[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]boss battle[/b][/color] has been added, [u]craft and use[/u] the [color=#ffff00][b]Deep Earth Orb[/b][/color] to initiate it at the [color=#00ff00][b]mine's entrance[/b][/color].
● A new piece of [color=#ffff00][b]equipment[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Mistpool Pickaxe[/b][/color], has been added. It [color=#00ffff][b]scales dynamically[/b][/color] similar to the [color=#00ff00][b]Mistpool[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]weapon[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color] and is the [u]only pickaxe[/u] available for use by [u]default[/u]. (This may be changed in the newly added [u]configuration file[/u]).[/size][/left]

[center][size=4][b][i]System Changes[/i][/b][/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [color=#00ffff][b]Music[/b][/color] in the [b][color=#ff00ff]Deep Dungeon[/color][/b] is now [u]randomized[/u] each floor. (This may be toggled in the newly added [u]configuration file[/u]).
● The [color=#ff7700][b]HP Penalty[/b][/color] [color=#00ffff][b]floor enchantment[/b][/color] and new [color=#ffff00][b]Siphon Life[/b][/color] [b][color=#00ffff]spell[/color][/b] now [u]truly modify your maximum HP[/u] (temporarily) until you [u]leave the floor[/u]. To prevent this temporary modification from being accidentally persisted, [u]saving is disabled while inside[/u] the [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color].
● A [color=#ffff00][b]mod configuration file[/b][/color] that will allow you to [u]customize the mod[/u].
● Additional [color=#ffff00][b]optional files[/b][/color] for the mod change various [color=#ff00ff][b]Deep Dungeon[/b][/color] [color=#ffff00][b]items[/b][/color] that are [u]normally only craftable[/u] to [u]also be purchasable[/u] at the [color=#00ff00][b]Blacksmith's shop[/b][/color] for those not wanting to obtain them via the standard crafting progression route.[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Future Updates[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
This mod is still a work in progress. While there is no strict schedule for the full release, I intend to roll out the remaining content in iterative updates.[/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [b]v1.0[/b]: Additional kinds of [u]interactive[/u] [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color]. Hidden [color=#00ffff][b]treasure spots[/b][/color] on floors that drop extremely rare and powerful [color=#00ff00][b]Greater Sigils[/b][/color]. A new [u]special[/u] "advanced" [color=#ffff00][b]class[/b][/color], the [color=#00ff00][b]Oracle[/b][/color], which will have unique [color=#00ffff][b]spells[/b][/color] to trigger new kinds of [color=#00ffff][b]Floor Enchantments[/b][/color] and [color=#00ffff][b]Offerings[/b][/color]. Two new types of standard [color=#00ff00][b]Sigils[/b][/color], [color=#ffff00][b]Sight[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]Intuition[/b][/color]. The [b][color=#00ff00]Sigil of Sight[/color][/b] will [b][color=#00ffff]dispel darkness [/color][/b]and [color=#00ffff][b]reveal trap locations[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor. The [b][color=#00ff00]Sigil of Intuition[/color][/b] will [color=#00ffff][b]reveal the hidden treasure spot[/b][/color] on the current dungeon floor.
● [b]v1.1+[/b]: Chaotic [color=#ff00ff][b]boss battles[/b][/color], using the [u]interactive[/u] [color=#ff7700][b]floor traps[/b][/color] for unique battle sequences.
[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Shout-Outs & Credits[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
This mod has a large amount of custom code and sprite assets added to the game. Several other people were commissioned and involved with different aspects of this mod. This section is to recognize their work and thank them for an incredible job![/size][/center][left][size=3]
● [b]Annanomoly[/b]: Mod author. C++ code development and overall design.
● [b]Stampingfeet[/b]: Mod contributor. Created the [color=#ffff00][b]mistpool weapon[/b][/color] and [color=#ffff00][b]armor[/b][/color] sprite assets, the [color=#ffff00][b]key[/b][/color] sprite assets, the [color=#ffff00][b]orb[/b][/color] sprite assets, and the [color=#ffff00][b]class gear[/b][/color] sprite assets.
● [b]Crys[/b]: Mod contributor. Created the [color=#ffff00][b]sigil[/b][/color] and [b][color=#ffff00]soul stone[/color][/b] sprite assets.
● [b]Kathulhu[/b]: Mod contributor. Created the [color=#ffff00][b]salve[/b][/color] sprite assets. Created the [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fieldsofmistria/mods/481]Sailor Mistria Set[/url], [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fieldsofmistria/mods/486]Princess Twintails Hair[/url], and [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/fieldsofmistria/mods/512]Astral Dimsum Hair Set[/url] [color=#00ffff][b]cosmetic[/b][/color] mods featured in the preview videos and images of this mod.
● [b]Chris Mzz[/b]: Mod contributor. Created the [b][color=#ff00ff]dread beast[/color][/b] attack patterns and discovered how to customize [color=#ff00ff][b]monsters[/b][/color]. Math wizard!
● [b]Gareth[/b]: Creator of [url=https://github.com/Garethp/Mods-of-Mistria-Installer]MOMI[/url]﻿. Without it, this mod would not be possible.
● [b]Archie[/b]: Creator of [url=https://github.com/AurieFramework/Aurie]Aurie [/url]﻿& [url=https://github.com/AurieFramework/YYToolkit]YYTK[/url]﻿. Without it, this mod would not be possible.
● [b]Jack[/b]: Technical guidance and moral support. For opening modding up more for the community.[/size][/left]


[center][size=6][b][u]Feedback & Bug Reporting[/u][/b][/size][/center][center][size=3]
This mod is essentially in [u]early access[/u], much like the game. There are bound to be bugs you will encounter. If you do encounter a bug, please post a [u]comment[/u] and/or submit a [u]bug report[/u]. If possible, paste the contents of the [b]YYToolkit.log[/b] in your post so that I can debug what happened. The log file is in the same directory as the game executable. Below is an example of the section from the log file that will be most helpful. Note that there may be [u]multiple[/u] errors and stacktraces, please provide the [u]first[/u] one at minimum.[/size][/center][size=3]
[code]
A fatal game error has occured.
Runner caught the exception; the exception_unhandled_handler callback has not been invoked.

Runner-given error information:
